# iOS Build Standards

## Standard Simulator
Always use iPhone 16: `D9DE6784-CB62-4AC3-A686-4D445A0E7B57`

## Build Command
Always use the build script:
```bash
cd rn-mip-app
npm run build:ios:release
```

This script:
1. Boots iPhone 16 simulator
2. Runs clean build in Release mode
3. Installs and launches the app

## NEVER USE
- `npx expo run:ios` - causes stale code issues and wrong simulator targeting
- `booted` as device target - always use explicit UDID

## Screenshots
```bash
xcrun simctl io D9DE6784-CB62-4AC3-A686-4D445A0E7B57 screenshot /tmp/screenshot.png
```

## Install/Launch (without rebuild)
```bash
xcrun simctl install D9DE6784-CB62-4AC3-A686-4D445A0E7B57 ios/build/Build/Products/Release-iphonesimulator/FFCIMobile.app
xcrun simctl launch D9DE6784-CB62-4AC3-A686-4D445A0E7B57 com.fiveq.ffci
```
